    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is mitigated by the direct correspondence of the single F1717 loading condition to the intended COU loading and by the strong quantitative agreement across all three QoIs (E/uval < 1.96, difference < 10%). Uncertainty quantification across material and geometric inputs has been completed via Monte Carlo propagation, confirming that aggregate output uncertainty is within acceptable bounds. The package is accepted for regulatory submission with the acknowledged test conditions gap documented.",
